# React Component Patterns

## Component Structure

```tsx
// ✅ Named export, typed props, descriptive file = component name
type CardProps = {
  title: string
  description?: string
  children?: React.ReactNode
  className?: string
}

export function Card({ title, description, children, className }: CardProps) {
  return (
    <div className={cn('rounded-lg border p-6', className)}>
      <h3 className="font-semibold text-lg">{title}</h3>
      {description && <p className="text-gray-500 mt-1">{description}</p>}
      {children}
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Custom Hooks

Extract stateful logic into `src/hooks/` or co-located `use*.ts` files:

```ts
// src/hooks/useLocalStorage.ts
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react'

export function useLocalStorage<T>(key: string, initial: T) {
  const [value, setValue] = useState<T>(initial)

  useEffect(() => {
    const stored = localStorage.getItem(key)
    if (stored) setValue(JSON.parse(stored) as T)
  }, [key])

  const set = (next: T) => {
    setValue(next)
    localStorage.setItem(key, JSON.stringify(next))
  }

  return [value, set] as const
}
```

## Performance

```tsx
// ✅ Memoize expensive child renders
import { memo, useCallback } from 'react'

const ExpensiveList = memo(function ExpensiveList({ items }: { items: string[] }) {
  return <ul>{items.map(i => <li key={i}>{i}</li>)}</ul>
})

// ✅ Stable callback references for frequently re-rendering parents
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  doSomething(id)
}, [id])
```

## Rules

- One component per file; filename = component name (PascalCase)
- Default export only for page files (`app/**/page.tsx`); named exports elsewhere
- Never mutate props or state directly
- `key` on list items must be stable and unique — never array index for dynamic lists
- Avoid `useEffect` for data fetching — use Server Components or SWR/React Query
